Abandonded child syndrome is the behavioural or psychological attributes that a child develops as a result of one or both parents disappearing from their lives.  It is very similar in nature to [[post traumatic stress]] syndrome, and symptoms include:-


1.  Alienation from their environment;

2.  Extreme changes in state of mind and depression;

3.  Guilt;

4.  Fear and uncertainty;

5.  Sleep and eating disorders;

6.  Physical ailments, such as fatigue.


Children tend to relive the shocking event by way of games or play because the role of imagination of much greater for young people.  Typically, abandoned children become increasingly guiet or aggressive, out or control, or hard to handle.


Serial killers who were abandoned include:-


1.  Mary Bell;

2.  Jeffery Dahmer;

3.  Charles Manson.


Many children suffering from abandoned child syndrome are society's [[thrown away children]].  They are children who have left home of their own accord or were forced out of their homes because the rejection, neglect, and/or abuse was so great.